<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="plate_reader">Plate Reader</a> - A device for measuring the <a href="#absorbance">absorbance</a>, luminescence, or <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescence</a> of bulk cell culture, <em>exempli gratia</em> suspended <a href="#bacteria">bacteria</a>. The name comes from reading the values of these properties in standard multi-well plate format, <em>exempli gratia</em> 96-well plates, where each well contains a sample.